      "page_number": 1,
      "raw_text": "WASHINGTON, d. c., Dec. 2S.-\nRoosevelt has wired Gov. Sparks\nthat he would delay calling the fed\neral troops from Goldfield for five\ndays If in the meantime Sparks\nwould call special session OF the\nlegislature to arrange for the\nstate handling the situation. Roose-\nwelt thinks five days Is SUFFICIENT.\nThe delay was secured by Sen.\nNewlands acting on behalf of the\nmine owners.\n\n\nNewlands appealed to Taft and\nRoot with the result that a courier\nwas dispatched to Pine Knot, where\nthe president is spending the holi-\ndays."
    }
  ]
